{
  "texts": [
    "As deep learning techniques continue to improve, we can expect to see even more accurate and effective emotion recognition in the future.FER2013 is among the most popular databases and contains 35,887 images that have been resized to 48 × 48 pixels.",
    "These images were collected from Google image search API [132].",
    "AffectNet [133] is another significant database that contains both categorical and dimensional models of facial expressions.",
    "It comprises over one million images gathered from various search engines on the internet.",
    "Most FER databases typically classify emotions into the six fundamental expressions of happiness, anger, sadness, surprise, disgust, and fear, as well as a neutral state."
  ]
}